[1]
Date: 25 May 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Orlando Sentinel, 25 May 2005 [edited]
<http://www.orlandosentinel.com/news/local/newsletter/mu-html/orl-bk-
canker052505,0,363553.story>

Canker outbreak confirmed in Polk County
----------------------------------------
The suspected outbreak of citrus canker (CC) in Polk County was
confirmed by genetic testing today [25 May 2005], said Denise D.
Feiber, spokeswoman for the Division of Plant Industry in the Florida
Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services. The dreaded disease,
confirmed as Asian citrus canker, causes premature leaf and fruit
drop.
Officials must burn all trees within 1900 feet of a tree spotted with
CC. Workers at a Ben Hill Griffin Inc. nursery in Frostproof spotted
the suspected canker tree more than one week ago. Feiber said earlier
that more than 5000 trees will be burned, based on the initial
finding. It will be about a week before officials know how many trees
in total will be destroyed.
[Byline: Amy L. Edwards]
